headlines.description: — LaMelo Ball had 32 points and 10 rebounds, Miles Bridges added 21 points and the Charlotte Hornets snapped a 10-game losing streak with a 115-104 win over the Phoenix Suns on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaMelo Ball scores 32 points as Hornets defeat Suns 115-104 to snap 10-game losing streak

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored 22 of his 29 points in the third quarter and the Houston Rockets routed the short-handed Washington Wizards 135-112 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green scores 22 of his 29 in 3rd quarter as Rockets down Wizards 135-112

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Quinten Grimes had 26 points, nine rebounds and six assists as the Dallas Mavericks snapped a five-game skid with a 118-97 win over the Los Angeles Lakers on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mavericks end 5-game losing streak with a 118-97 victory over Lakers

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards highlighted a 32-point performance with seven 3-pointers, and the Minnesota Timberwolves beat the New Orleans Pelicans 104-97 on Tuesday night to take some luster off of Zion Williamson's return from a 27-game absence.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Edwards scores 32 and the Timberwolves top the Pelicans 104-97 in Zion Williamson's return

headlines.description: — Trae Young hit a buzzer-beating 3-pointer from beyond the halfcourt line to give the Atlanta Hawks a 124-121 victory over the Utah Jazz on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trae Young's 49-foot buzzer-beater lifts Hawks to a 124-121 win over the Jazz

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 29 points, Kristaps Porzingis added 25 and the Boston Celtics held off the depleted Denver Nuggets 118-106 on Tuesday night as three-time NBA MVP <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Jayson Tatum scores 29, Porzingis adds 25 as Celtics hold off depleted Nuggets 118-106

events.name: Miami Heat at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo had 19 points, nine rebounds and five assists with two timely dunks down the stretch, and the Miami Heat snapped a three-game losing streak by beating the Golden State Warriors 114-98 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bam Adebayo leads Heat past Warriors 114-98 in back-to-back after double-OT loss at Sacramento
